==English==

===Noun===

'''marl'''

#A mixed earthy substance, consisting of [[carbonate of lime]], clay, and possibly sand, in very variable proportions, and accordingly designated as calcareous, clayey, or sandy. See Greensand.

====Quotations====
*'''2004''': Those loved unhappy shades whom Dante turned / To sticks and '''marl'''  &mdash; Peter Porter, 'Why Did Dante Pick on Suicides', from ''Afterburner,'' 2004.

===Verb===

'''to marl'''

#To cover, as part of a rope, with marline, marking a pecular hitch at each turn to prevent unwinding.